	Kuala Lumpur, Jan. 20 (PTI): The Malaysian Prime Minister today declared the Hindu festival of Thaipusam a national holiday, assuaging the feelings of agitated ethnic Indians ahead of elections.
    
	Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said he made the decision after getting requests from the ethnic Indian community. 
                                                                                
